EA+BF&=b\cos{A}+b\cos{B}=x'(-\cos{A}-\cos{B}-\cos{(A+B}))\\
EA+BF&=-b(\cos{A}+\cos{B})-a\cos{C}\\
\cos{A}+\cos{B}&=-a\cos{c}/(b(\cos{A}+\cos{B}+a\cos{C}))
\end{align*}
Now, we have an equation with two cosine terms on the left-hand side. However, we can use the sum-to-product identity to express the sum of two cosine terms as a product of two sine terms and a cosine term. Therefore, we have:
\begin{align*}
2\cos{(\theta_1-\theta_2)}&=2(\cos{(\theta_1)}\cos{(\theta_2)}+\sin{(\theta_1)}\sin{(\theta_2)}) 
2\cos{(\theta_1-\theta_2)}&=2(\cos{(\theta_1)}\cos{(\theta_2)}+\sin{(\theta_1)}\sin{(\theta_2)})
\end{align*}
Therefore, we can express EA+BF = $ timESin{Sing}sin{C$ as:
\begin{align*}
EA+BF&=-b(\cos{A}+\cos{B})-a\cos{C}\\
+b(\cos{A}+\cos{B})+a\cos{C}&=timESin{Sing}sin{C\\
timESin{Sing}sin{C}&=a\cos{C}\\
\sin{C}&=\frac{a\cos{C}}{timESin{Sing}sin{C}
\end{align*}
